    "id": "ssc_2018_q43",
    "question": "Pipes A and B can fill a tank in one hour and two hours respectively while pipe C can empty the filled up tank in one hour and fifteen minutes. A and C are turned on together at 9 a.m. After 2 hours, only A is closed and B is turned on. When will the tank be emptied?",
    "options": {
      "A": "11:30 am.",
      "B": "12:10 pm.",
      "C": "12:20 pm. 10:30 am.",
      "D": ""
    },
    "correctAnswer": "C",
    "correctValue": "12:20 pm. 10:30 am.",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "topic": "time_work",
    "year": 2018,
    "exam": "SSC CGL",
    "explanation": "Step 1: Find each pipe's rate: fill rate = 1/(time to fill), empty rate = 1/(time to empty).\nStep 2: Net rate when pipes A and C are open = rate A − rate C (since C empties).\nStep 3: Track work done in each time interval; find when tank becomes empty/full.\nFinal Answer: 12:20 pm. 10:30 am."
  },
