    "id": "ssc_2018_q54",
    "question": "The efficiencies of A, B and C are in the ratio 5 : 3 : 8. Working together they can complete a work in 30 days. A and B worked together for 20 days. The remaining work will be completed by C alone in:",
    "options": {
      "A": "40 days",
      "B": "36 days",
      "C": "30 days",
      "D": "32 days"
    },
    "correctAnswer": "A",
    "correctValue": "40 days",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "topic": "ratio",
    "year": 2018,
    "exam": "SSC CGL",
    "explanation": "Step 1: Combined efficiency = 5+3+8 = 16 parts.\nStep 2: Total work = 16 × 20 = 320 units.\nStep 3: Find the required person's efficiency and divide total work by it.\nFinal Answer: 40 days"
  },
  {
    "id": "ssc_2018_q56",
    "question": "The distance between two stations A and B is 800 km. A train X starts from A and moves towards B at 40 km/h and another train Y starts from B and moves towards A at 60 km/h. How far from A will they cross each other ?",
    "options": {
      "A": "380 km",
      "B": "320 km",
      "C": "300 km",
      "D": "360 km"
    },
    "correctAnswer": "B",
    "correctValue": "320 km",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "topic": "speed_distance",
    "year": 2018,
    "exam": "SSC CGL",
    "explanation": "Step 1: Trains move towards each other: relative speed = 40+60 = 100 km/h.\nStep 2: Time to meet = Distance / Relative speed = 800/100 = 8.00 h.\nStep 3: Distance covered by train X from A = 40 × 8.00 = 320 km.\nFinal Answer: 320 km"
  },
